Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Model V1 - Self-Balancing Tail with Variable Length", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.929354612578005*^9, 3.929354616192994*^9}, {
  3.929355210549653*^9, 3.9293552190879917`*^9}, {3.9918429510719347`*^9, 
  3.991842958992612*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"067356c3-28ca-4144-be02-\
7957e03610f3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Before changing the angle of the tail or adding more joints, we need to \
understand how balance works. In physics, balance is achieved by having a net \
torque of zero in our system. In this case, our system is defined as the \
following: with a center of mass for the tail offset by a distance and a \
center of mass for the head offset by a distance and height. For all \
calculations, we will use SI units.\n\nFrom this setup, we must derive an \
equation that can be used. In this setup, the six main variables are:\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "d3a218c4-41f3-43af-8251-ca126d82a3b6"],
 " - the mass of the head.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "head"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "043508de-5fd4-4e73-a986-381fe8f39b7a"],
 " - the horizontal distance from the point mass of the head to the body.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "head"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "2d5bdb53-56df-4057-9d10-36d835a93931"],
 " - the vertical distance from the point mass of the head to the body.\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "e04d9068-6d37-40ba-b60d-05dae9824814"],
 " - the mass of the tail.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "bdf3ce6d-0887-4132-9f5f-f159b10b1aeb"],
 " - the horizontal distance from the point mass of the tail to the body. It\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s important to note that the center of mass for the tail is \
this value divided by two as it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s not a point mass.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "e23a3094-eee7-4171-8c24-bf53ce777e70"],
 " - the vertical distance from the point mass of the tail to the body.\n\n\
However, our monkey will not always be standing. Thus, we need to factor in a \
7th variable, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9014cda8-3bed-4c8e-8ae7-cc15cd3e73ca"],
 ". In our diagram, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "88e7eff0-baa4-4419-83f5-9eb70d30513e"],
 " looks like this:\n\nWith the variables setup, we can begin calculations. \
Because there are only two masses in the system, the head and the tail, the \
torque equation looks like this: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cd99f442-28cb-4c6f-bc85-4796c408e252"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "817a813e-0a10-4092-83da-c383120e1fc3"],
 "\n\nSubstituting in the equation that torque is \[Tau] = F*r*sin(\[Theta]), \
we can calculate our radii (r) as this:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "60ae99d5-91bf-4f1f-b23e-c13bfd7fcd07"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      SubscriptBox["d", "head"], "2"], " ", "+", " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      SubscriptBox["h", "head"], "2"]}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "e6c70c5c-cbda-49a5-821f-4a5161a3717e"],
 "\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "12cddac9-a804-4811-94b0-0aac5322853c"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox[
        SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], "2"], ")"}], "2"], " ", "+", " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], "2"]}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "ddf1b52a-f8c3-4576-b6ab-26325d881ece"],
 "\n\nCalculating for \[Theta] is slightly harder. The angle for the \
components of gravity is not the exact angle that the radius makes with the \
long leg & short leg of the triangle. We can use alternate interior angles to \
model the system as the following, with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3bfd5ab1-43ff-4996-bf70-862875fbd56d"],
 " as the temporary one representing the \[Theta] in the head equation and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "t"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "217b9b72-a604-4a0b-86b7-93034fc212d5"],
 " representing the tail equation. Using trigonometric identities, both of \
these will eventually be replaced.\n\n\nWith ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "t"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e2599c8f-2b23-4e35-a390-5b89975eb1a6"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4e7e04f8-dbee-49c0-b09d-a0c2273e4285"],
 " defined, we can plug them into the torque equations and simplify from \
there. Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s begin with the head equation.\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a4d1b42b-5f5a-4420-929b-29d115249527"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a2e7d326-8113-4b1e-9a75-169aa46c8218"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "14bac94c-5994-4694-8ff8-f25113d52dfe"],
 " * sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "23ef66f7-cd9a-4586-bc22-41dddf3de4f1"],
 ")\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f69dc05c-d103-45e5-bbf9-f097ec217f0b"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "80e30a3a-92f0-4ab9-911f-79fcbe564736"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ee57d3f1-5e8b-44b9-9861-46ef566d1aa0"],
 " * sin(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "70757adb-b720-42d6-9200-7bd2fd5bd3a0"],
 ")+",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "336ba21a-88e3-4391-9155-b2c47327cdc1"],
 ")\n\nInside of the sine function is an addition of two angles. Using this, \
we can expand, and then simplify it with the sum of sines identity:\nsin(A+B) \
= sinAcosB + cosAsinB\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d032c627-6707-48e5-8e93-f3f256ae1b0b"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c60add9e-93f0-4014-b517-2c2ffb4c2466"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8650b8d5-3a1d-430a-b284-2dbfa76233ce"],
 " * sin(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "d7e28702-f37c-4cdd-8e0f-86d8f0e93e76"],
 ")+",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "83674518-905c-4011-a476-94ff3c2e8625"],
 ")\n\|01d70f_head = m_head * r_head * \
(sin(arctan(d_head/h_head))cos(\[Theta]_lean)+cos(arctan(d_head/h_head))sin(\
\[Theta]_lean))\n\nIt seems complex, but the sine and cosine \
arctan(d_head/h_head) can actually be defined using r_head! Let\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s examine that with the diagram below:\n\nWe end up with:\n\
\nsin(arctan(d_head/h_head)) = d_head/r_head\ncos(arctan(d_head/h_head)) = \
h_head/r_head\n\nGiven this, let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s plug it in to the \
equation.\n\|01d70f_head = m_head * r_head * ( (d_head * \
cos(\[Theta]_lean)/r_head) +(h_head * sin(\[Theta]_lean)/r_head))\n\nSince \
every part of the identity has r_head on the denominator, and we are \
multiplying it by r_head, we get a much simpler equation for the torque of \
the head:\n\n\|01d70f_head = m_head * r_head * ( d_head * cos(\[Theta]_lean) \
+ h_head * sin(\[Theta]_lean))\n\nThe torque of the tail is the same, except \
instead of adding the two angles, we must subtract them, as the diagram \
shows. This means we use the difference of sines identity, sin(A-B) = \
sinAcosB-cosAsinB. We also must remember that the distance (d_head) is \
divided by two:\n\n\|01d70f_tail = m_tail * r_tail * sin(\[Theta]_t)\n\
\|01d70f_tail = m_tail * r_tail * sin(arctan(d_tail/2h_tail)-\[Theta]_lean)\n\
\|01d70f_tail = m_tail * r_tail * \
(sin(arctan(d_tail/2h_tail))cos(\[Theta]_lean)-cos(arctan(d_tail/2h_tail))sin(\
\[Theta]_lean))\n\|01d70f_head = m_head * r_head * ( (d_tail * \
cos(\[Theta]_lean)/2r_head) -(h_tail * sin(\[Theta]_lean)/r_head))\n\
\|01d70f_head = m_head * r_head * ( (d_tail * cos(\[Theta]_lean)/2) -h_tail * \
sin(\[Theta]_lean))\n\nThe finished model is the following, where we set both \
torques equal to each other.\n\n\|01d70f_head = m_head * r_head * ( d_head * \
cos(\[Theta]_lean) + h_head * sin(\[Theta]_lean)) = \|01d70f_head = m_head * \
r_head * ( (d_tail * cos(\[Theta]_lean)/2) -h_tail * sin(\[Theta]_lean)).\n\n\
\nTo model the monkey tilting itself, we must change \[Theta]_tail. If we \
changed \[Theta]_tail, the system would just fall. To accommodate for this, \
we must make one or more of the six variables unknown such that the model can \
automatically adjust it to keep the torques in equilibrium. In this example, \
we will solve for d_tail as our unknown variable.\n\nThis will be achieved \
with the Wolfram Language. To start the simulation, we define the constants = \
all variables besides d_tail."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9293546184036617`*^9, 3.9293546199188967`*^9}, {
   3.991843023893482*^9, 3.991843098671399*^9}, {3.991843141651308*^9, 
   3.991843153204752*^9}, {3.9918432145448112`*^9, 3.991843314639442*^9}, {
   3.991843367531785*^9, 3.991843482849601*^9}, {3.991843529523225*^9, 
   3.991843563288316*^9}, {3.99184359410602*^9, 3.9918436278691387`*^9}, {
   3.9918436914439497`*^9, 3.991843723147058*^9}, {3.991843789397196*^9, 
   3.9918438381344337`*^9}, {3.99184392692651*^9, 3.991844022786091*^9}, {
   3.991844093496125*^9, 3.9918441019339437`*^9}, {3.991844140124487*^9, 
   3.991844288216073*^9}, {3.991844434010304*^9, 3.991844463089705*^9}, 
   3.991844536742257*^9, {3.991844571327832*^9, 3.991844681795814*^9}, {
   3.991844719772691*^9, 3.9918447236166487`*^9}, {3.99184475520887*^9, 
   3.991844812664764*^9}, {3.991900660775463*^9, 3.991900688971546*^9}, {
   3.991900729486137*^9, 3.9919007895352983`*^9}, {3.991901415519161*^9, 
   3.991901558521984*^9}, {3.991901612081134*^9, 3.991901873321487*^9}, {
   3.991901966594462*^9, 3.991902031905037*^9}, {3.991902066001555*^9, 
   3.991902119420312*^9}, {3.991902164200292*^9, 3.9919022705054607`*^9}, {
   3.99190278807376*^9, 3.9919028913216267`*^9}, {3.99190293358051*^9, 
   3.991903134249188*^9}, {3.9919032240534286`*^9, 3.991903324589549*^9}, {
   3.9919034062311087`*^9, 3.991903419125595*^9}, {3.991903471088574*^9, 
   3.991903597660206*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9b79198e-7897-462b-8630-\
68f1f3d31553"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"g", " ", "=", " ", "9.81"}], ";"}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   RowBox[{"m", "/", "s"}], "*)"}], "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"mHead", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ";"}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", "kg", "*)"}]}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"dHead", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ";"}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", "m", "*)"}]}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"hHead", " ", "=", " ", "5"}], ";"}], "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"mTail", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ";"}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", "kg", "*)"}]}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"hTail", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ";"}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", "m", "*)"}], "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "=", " ", "15"}], ";"}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", "degrees", "*)"}]}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991815092339835*^9, 3.991815096115572*^9}, {
  3.9918152291416388`*^9, 3.991815314520664*^9}, {3.991838032309401*^9, 
  3.9918380970051413`*^9}, {3.991838130860958*^9, 3.991838183760466*^9}, {
  3.9918382336683683`*^9, 3.991838234485955*^9}, {3.991838564647468*^9, 
  3.99183857774774*^9}, {3.991839635590024*^9, 3.991839652727968*^9}, {
  3.991839684969195*^9, 3.991839685059473*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[10]:=",ExpressionUUID->"8b316891-cc46-4475-8f26-493f8b82e012"],

Cell["\<\
We then set up the model defined above using the NSolve function, which can \
automatically solve for unknowns, such as d_tail, in an equation. Doing that \
with the above parameters yields the following result.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.99190227519729*^9, 3.991902275854611*^9}, {
  3.991902348282752*^9, 
  3.9919023868802967`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b4eb0987-774e-46ca-a39b-\
6c88bb75d9de"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"NSolve", "[", "\n", "\t", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"mHead", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"dHead", "*", 
        RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
         RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}], "+", 
       RowBox[{"hHead", "*", 
        RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
         RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}], ")"}]}], "==", 
    RowBox[{"mTail", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{"dTail", "*", 
           RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
            RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}], ")"}], "/", "2"}], 
        ")"}], "-", 
       RowBox[{"hTail", "*", 
        RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
         RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}], ")"}]}]}], ",", 
   "\n", "\t", "dTail"}], "]"}]], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.991840322657197*^9, {3.9919023631853228`*^9, 3.9919023641122837`*^9}, 
   3.991907599137916*^9, 3.991907651080515*^9},
 CellLabel->"In[8]:=",ExpressionUUID->"4eeea633-52f6-439f-94ba-b07cf20edf7f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"dTail", "\[Rule]", "5.215390309173472`"}], "}"}], "}"}]], "Output",\

 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991840497576198*^9, 3.991840502418158*^9}, 
   3.991841178107341*^9, {3.991841314979292*^9, 3.991841334582686*^9}, 
   3.9918416813661757`*^9, 3.991900211625662*^9, 3.991900408715494*^9, 
   3.9919025781511993`*^9, 3.9919073042816153`*^9, {3.9919075761124783`*^9, 
   3.991907576324671*^9}, {3.9919076541679163`*^9, 3.991907674988295*^9}, 
   3.99190775217782*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[8]=",ExpressionUUID->"bb83496d-ae6f-4ad0-9102-610555beb781"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
The final part of this simple model is to form the real-time simulation. To \
do this, we must have an input to change \[Theta]_lean. This as a result \
should change the rotation of the monkey and the tail length of the monkey. \
The DynamicModule function achieves the real-time input we desire, and the \
Graphics function can draw out our monkey out of lines defined by the \
variables. The simulation\[CloseCurlyQuote]s code and output are visualized \
below.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.99190238955822*^9, 3.991902394104595*^9}, {
  3.991902430632996*^9, 
  3.9919025364622602`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6fc34f11-1b3e-4bc2-9017-\
3c666fb52d40"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"DynamicModule", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"dTail", "=", "1"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"thetaLeanString", "=", "\"\<\[Theta]_lean = \>\""}]}], "}"}], ",",
    "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"Column", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", "\n", "\t\t", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Slider", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Dynamic", "[", "thetaLean", "]"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"-", "89.9"}], ",", "89.9"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ",", "\n", 
      "\t\t", 
      RowBox[{"Dynamic", "[", 
       RowBox[{"StringJoin", "[", 
        RowBox[{"thetaLeanString", " ", ",", " ", 
         RowBox[{"ToString", "[", "thetaLean", "]"}], ",", 
         " ", "\"\<\[Degree]\>\""}], "]"}], "]"}], ",", "\n", "\t\t", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"dTail", "=", 
        RowBox[{"Dynamic", "[", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Values", "[", 
            RowBox[{"NSolve", "[", "\n", "\t\t\t", 
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{
               RowBox[{"mHead", 
                RowBox[{"(", 
                 RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"dHead", "*", 
                   RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}], "+", 
                  RowBox[{"hHead", "*", 
                   RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}], ")"}]}], 
               "==", 
               RowBox[{"mTail", 
                RowBox[{"(", 
                 RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"(", 
                   RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"(", 
                    RowBox[{"dTail", "*", 
                    RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}], ")"}], "/",
                     "2"}], ")"}], "-", 
                  RowBox[{"hTail", "*", 
                   RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
                    RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}], 
                 ")"}]}]}], ",", "\n", "\t\t\t", "dTail"}], "\n", "\t\t", 
             "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], ",", "\n", "\t\t", 
      RowBox[{"Graphics", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"Blue", ",", "\n", "\t\t\t", 
          RowBox[{"Dynamic", "[", 
           RowBox[{"Rotate", "[", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{
               RowBox[{"Line", "[", 
                RowBox[{"{", 
                 RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                   RowBox[{"0", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", 
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                   RowBox[{"0", ",", "hHead"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}], ",", 
               RowBox[{"Line", "[", 
                RowBox[{"{", 
                 RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                   RowBox[{"0", ",", "hTail"}], "}"}], ",", 
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                   RowBox[{"dTail", ",", "hTail"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}], ",", 
               RowBox[{"Line", "[", 
                RowBox[{"{", 
                 RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                   RowBox[{"0", ",", "hHead"}], "}"}], ",", 
                  RowBox[{"{", 
                   RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{"-", "dHead"}], ",", "hHead"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], 
