Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Model V2 - Self-Balancing Tail with Variable Rotation", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.929354612578005*^9, 3.929354616192994*^9}, {
  3.929355210549653*^9, 3.9293552190879917`*^9}, {3.9918429510719347`*^9, 
  3.991842958992612*^9}, {3.991902603837475*^9, 
  3.99190260972873*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e8a0458b-9a9a-4f2c-b0e2-\
e43b9f94ed10"],

Cell["\<\
Our model now works, however it is inaccurate to any \
animal\[CloseCurlyQuote]s behavior in nature. An animal cannot grow or shrink \
its tail in real-time. Instead, to counterbalance its mass, it will change \
the angle of its tail. To achieve this, we need to adjust our model and \
define a new constant for the angle of the tail, \[Theta]_dynamic.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9293546184036617`*^9, 3.9293546199188967`*^9}, {
